ygData.msgSnippet: Fippy is the one that spawns in North Qeynos.  A GM also takes the place of Fippy every so often and will talk to you.  This I am positive...here is Fippy s
ygData.messageBody:
Fippy is the one that spawns in North Qeynos. A GM
also takes the place of Fippy every so often and will
talk to you. This I am positive...here is Fippy's website
you can see for yourself.

http://home.pacbell.net/graeing/index.html

> >
> >Uhmm - Fippy is the low level npc in nq - of that I am certain! Now
> Flippy
> >is probably the one you speak of and I have seen Verant play other tricks
> >with similar names to entice you into fights way over your head. GM's
> can
> >take over NPC's and play them against players - not sure what their
> policy
> >is but they have the power. I have heard that they will do this to break
>
> >up
> >farmers who are not sharing spawns at camp sites.
> >
> >You can hail Gnasher Gnoll as well and talk to him. He is part of 2
> quests
> >out of Qeynos. And much lower level than the uber Gnolls in BB.
> >
> >There is another named gnoll who lives on the farm in West Karana. His
> >name
> >is Furball Miller. You can talk to him too. (Hint: just don't blindly
> >follow him into the corn fields.) Also talking to his parents you get
> his
> >sad tale. He is adopted. I think this is some unfinished quest as he
> has
> >relations back in BlackBurrow or Split Paw.
> >
> >In South Qeynos there is a quest to kill Trumpy Irontoe - an obnoxious
> >short
> >guy. In QH, you will see a Crumpy Irontoe who is much higher level. I
> >think Verant wants to fool you into trying to kill him thinking its
> Trumpy
> >(low level) when really it's Crumpy (high level) and you will get your
> butt
> >kicked (unless of course you are high level.)
> >
> >Moral of the story: con everything and read the words as well as look at
> >the
> >colors.
> >
> >Snyak.
> >
> >

> > and the second being a GM of verant who spawns himself up
> >top of
> > blackburrow. Fippy is lvl 17, and if u catch him in a good
> >mood and hail him
> > speaking Gnoll he will actually talk to...
> > i was told this by a apprentice gm one day and i didn't
> >believe him... so i
> > went and waited in BB after paying 5pp to learn Gnoll..
> > 1day went by and no Fippy
> > 2day and no Fippy
> > and on the 3rd day i just happened to be at the right place
> >and the right
> > time...FIPPY SPAWNED. then after a short conversation he
> >proceeded to kick
> > my butt...
> > Moral of the Story
> > I have no clue but it was neat talking to him..
